WEBVTT

00:00.671 --> 00:02.049
Previously on...

00:02.073 --> 00:04.590
Sounds to me as if someone's
let go of his rage.

00:04.614 --> 00:07.554
Maybe I have. Well, ihaven't.

00:07.578 --> 00:10.057
Felicia took matters
into her own hands.

00:10.081 --> 00:12.319
You want me to call off
the wedding, I'll do it.

00:12.343 --> 00:14.770
I'll do whatever you want. Karl
put the ball in Susan's court...

00:14.794 --> 00:17.724
With your d.U.I. Charge,
it could get ugly.

00:17.748 --> 00:20.167
While Andrew tried
to take Bree to court...

00:20.191 --> 00:22.699
There's a father.
He's a kid!

00:22.723 --> 00:25.010
Gabrielle and Carlos took the baby...
The papers aren't valid anymore.

00:25.034 --> 00:27.504
Do you really wanna leave
this beautiful little girl

00:27.528 --> 00:29.736
with that
white trash freak show?

00:29.760 --> 00:31.260
And ran with it.

00:33.264 --> 00:37.084
Louisa pate
believed in the power of shame.

00:37.108 --> 00:38.585
As a teacher,

00:38.609 --> 00:41.017
she had found that the best way
to control unruly students

00:41.041 --> 00:44.591
was to instill
a strong sense of shame...

00:44.615 --> 00:46.293
In their parents.

00:46.317 --> 00:48.555
I left Trisha alone
with the school hamster

00:48.579 --> 00:50.279
for only five minutes.

00:52.083 --> 00:55.463
In this box
is all that's left of patches.

00:57.488 --> 01:00.537
For show and tell, Timmy decided
to bring in something

01:00.561 --> 01:04.101
from your husband's collection
of Nazi memorabilia.

01:06.237 --> 01:08.115
Billy's been threatening
to beat up the other kids

01:08.139 --> 01:09.616
for their milk money.

01:09.640 --> 01:11.640
We found the proceeds
in his cubby.

01:14.375 --> 01:16.353
Of course, Mrs. Pate also knew

01:16.377 --> 01:18.785
when it came to unruly children,

01:18.809 --> 01:22.129
some parents had more reason
to be ashamed...

01:22.153 --> 01:23.830
Than others.

01:23.854 --> 01:28.365
So, um... your message said
that Parker had been involved

01:28.389 --> 01:30.637
in some sort
of serious incident.

01:30.661 --> 01:32.068
What... what kind of incident?

01:32.092 --> 01:34.070
Yesterday afternoon,

01:34.094 --> 01:36.081
Parker offered a cookie
to Cindy Lou peeples

01:36.105 --> 01:39.176
if she would
show him her vagina.

01:39.200 --> 01:42.078
What kind of cookie?

01:42.102 --> 01:43.810
What does that matter?

01:43.834 --> 01:45.312
Oh, it doesn't.

01:45.336 --> 01:48.115
I'm just stalling because
I am completely mortified.

01:48.139 --> 01:51.118
The kids were in a broom closet.
Our janitor walked in on them

01:51.142 --> 01:54.561
just as Cindy was lifting up
her pinafore. Oh, my goodness.

01:54.585 --> 01:56.563
I'm sure you've noticed
how obsessive Parker can be.

01:56.587 --> 01:58.565
A certain subject
will catch his interest,

01:58.589 --> 02:01.168
and that's all he'll talk about
for weeks and weeks.

02:01.192 --> 02:03.530
Oh, right.
That happened with dinosaurs.

02:03.554 --> 02:05.541
Oh, yes, we all remember
his dinosaur phase.

02:05.565 --> 02:08.175
More fondly now than ever.

02:08.199 --> 02:12.239
Mm-hmm, so you think
that now he's obsessed with...

02:12.263 --> 02:14.420
What's underneath
the pinafore. Yes.

02:14.444 --> 02:17.314
Look, I think
he's just developed

02:17.338 --> 02:20.217
a normal curiosity
about the human body.

02:20.241 --> 02:22.289
You need to talk to him.

02:22.313 --> 02:24.256
Remind him what's appropriate
and what isn't.

02:24.280 --> 02:26.253
Of course. I will talk to him.

02:26.277 --> 02:28.555
I'll talk to him
till I'm blue in the face.

02:28.579 --> 02:30.657
I promise. Take care.

02:30.681 --> 02:35.302
Yes, Louisa pate believed
in the power of shame.

02:35.326 --> 02:38.535
She always believed,
when someone has that power...

02:38.559 --> 02:41.168
So, Mrs. Peeples,
you'll never guess

02:41.192 --> 02:44.179
what your daughter is willing
to do for a gingersnap.

02:44.203 --> 02:47.244
It's a shame not to use it.

02:47.268 --> 02:55.268
♪♪♪

03:30.511 --> 03:32.489
It had been six weeks

03:32.513 --> 03:35.822
since Andrew Van De Kamp
had declared war

03:35.846 --> 03:37.894
on his mother Bree.

03:37.918 --> 03:40.196
The final battle
was about to be waged

03:40.220 --> 03:42.369
at the Fairview county
courthouse.

03:42.393 --> 03:45.802
Bree knew
it was about to get bloody.

03:45.826 --> 03:48.635
What she didn't know was...

03:48.659 --> 03:51.708
The calvary was on its way...

03:51.732 --> 03:52.879
Bree?

03:52.903 --> 03:55.712
Whether she wanted them there
or not.

03:55.736 --> 03:56.983
Eleanor!

03:57.007 --> 03:59.816
Oh, thank god I found you.
This place is a maze.

03:59.840 --> 04:01.488
What are you doing here?

04:01.512 --> 04:04.996
Well, your father and I got
a call last night from Danielle,

04:05.020 --> 04:08.295
and she said that Andrew
was taking you to court.

04:08.319 --> 04:09.596
I mean,

04:09.620 --> 04:11.928
to say that we were shocked
would be an understatement.

04:11.952 --> 04:14.636
Hello, I'm Eleanor Mason,
Bree's stepmother.

04:14.660 --> 04:16.503
You're the lawyer?
We should talk.

04:16.527 --> 04:18.334
Uh, no, I'm not her lawyer.

04:18.358 --> 04:20.567
Good. The hair had me worried.

04:20.591 --> 04:23.270
Peter is mom's sponsor from a.A.

04:23.294 --> 04:25.412
Oh, sweetie!

04:25.436 --> 04:27.744
Since when are you in a.A.?

04:27.768 --> 04:29.946
It's a recent development.
Where's dad?

04:29.970 --> 04:32.279
In chambers with the judge.

04:32.303 --> 04:34.351
What?! Why?

04:34.375 --> 04:35.652
Everything is fine.

04:35.676 --> 04:37.784
The judge agreed
to a postponement.

04:37.808 --> 04:39.286
Oh, thank god!

04:39.310 --> 04:41.928
Luckily, he remembered me.
I spoke once at his law school.

04:41.952 --> 04:44.469
Pardon me, sir,
I'm your daughter's lawyer.

04:44.493 --> 04:45.962
Just so you know,

04:45.986 --> 04:48.495
we've been waiting
for this hearing for weeks,

04:48.519 --> 04:50.697
son, I've been an attorney
for 45 years.

04:50.721 --> 04:52.399
You and I both know

04:52.423 --> 04:54.980
how these cases can
turn into public spectacles.

04:55.004 --> 04:59.706
Our family is perfectly capable
of handling this in house.

04:59.730 --> 05:02.679
Dad, you don't understand.
This has gotten really ugly.

05:02.703 --> 05:04.611
That's why we're here.

05:04.635 --> 05:07.414
We're gonna put this family
back together.

05:07.438 --> 05:09.778
Whatever it takes.

05:14.845 --> 05:17.624
And that's
when Mr. and Mrs. Solis,

05:17.648 --> 05:20.026
fearing for the welfare
of this helpless child,

05:20.050 --> 05:21.628
fled the hospital.

05:21.652 --> 05:24.471
You mean, they kidnapped her.

05:24.495 --> 05:26.433
Well, technically, that's true,

05:26.457 --> 05:29.305
but given the situation
that led up to the rescue...

05:29.329 --> 05:31.638
Kidnapping.

05:31.662 --> 05:34.781
Your honor, yes, in retrospect,

05:34.805 --> 05:37.744
the plan was a little bit rash,
not entirely well thought out.

05:37.768 --> 05:38.845
Idiotic.

05:38.869 --> 05:41.448
Can we
object to that? Shh!

05:41.472 --> 05:43.450
But the childissafe, your honor.

05:43.474 --> 05:47.053
And all we ask the court
is to allow baby Lily

05:47.077 --> 05:49.926
a lifetime of the care and love

05:49.950 --> 05:52.880
she has been receiving
from the solises.

05:55.586 --> 05:58.665
As much as your story
tugs at my heart,

05:58.689 --> 06:00.737
there is the issue
of parental rights.

06:00.761 --> 06:02.709
What does the state
have to say about this?

06:02.733 --> 06:06.072
We have located
the biological father...

06:06.096 --> 06:07.574
Mr. Dale helm.

06:07.598 --> 06:10.717
Unfortunately, uh, circumstances
require that he be out of town.

06:10.741 --> 06:12.348
He's in Fort Lauderdale today.

06:12.372 --> 06:13.550
On business?

06:13.574 --> 06:15.722
Spring break, actually.

06:15.746 --> 06:17.724
Mr. Helm is
a high school student.

06:17.748 --> 06:21.528
Charming. In between keg stands,
did the father happen to mention

06:21.552 --> 06:25.432
if he plans
to waive parental rights?

06:25.456 --> 06:27.434
I've left
a number of voice mails,

06:27.458 --> 06:30.437
but the only response
I've gotten is a text message

06:30.461 --> 06:35.171
that says this "blows his mind"
and he's extremely "bummed out."

06:39.470 --> 06:41.848
All right...

06:41.872 --> 06:45.812
Mr. and Mrs. Solis,
since you actually want Lily,

06:45.836 --> 06:48.815
it seems you're
the lesser of two evils.

06:48.839 --> 06:50.957
I'm granting you
temporary custody

06:50.981 --> 06:54.390
until we can get a straight
answer from the birth father.

06:54.414 --> 06:56.423
Thank you, uh, your honor.

06:56.447 --> 06:59.566
In the meantime, try not
to steal any more babies.

06:59.590 --> 07:02.650
Oh, we just needed the one.

07:08.699 --> 07:10.977
Sweetie?

07:11.001 --> 07:13.510
Um, could you put
the crayons down for a second?

07:13.534 --> 07:15.682
We need to talk.

07:15.706 --> 07:17.183
So I spoke
to your teacher today,

07:17.207 --> 07:19.537
and she told me about the...

07:20.641 --> 07:23.790
Cookie deal
you made with Cindy Lou.

07:23.814 --> 07:26.052
Oh. Are you mad?

07:26.076 --> 07:29.556
No, not exactly.
I'm just...

07:29.580 --> 07:32.559
I'm trying to understand
why you...

07:32.583 --> 07:33.700
Did that.

07:33.724 --> 07:36.568
Tommy Keenan told me
babies come from down there.

07:36.592 --> 07:38.565
It doesn't sound right to me.

07:38.589 --> 07:40.537
Well...

07:40.561 --> 07:43.510
Actually, he's kinda right.
He's got the concept down.

07:43.534 --> 07:46.944
That's weird.
How's a baby get in there?

07:53.504 --> 07:56.491
Daddy will be home from
his business trip in a few days.

07:56.515 --> 07:58.485
Why don't you wait for him?

07:58.509 --> 08:00.909
Okay. Okay.

08:02.583 --> 08:04.631
Or I can ask Tommy's brother.

08:04.655 --> 08:08.255
He's 14,
and he knows everything.

08:10.821 --> 08:12.799
And then
the mommy and the daddy,

08:12.823 --> 08:14.950
because they love each other
so much,

08:14.974 --> 08:16.142
theyhug.

08:16.166 --> 08:18.605
Realtight.

08:18.629 --> 08:22.078
And, uh, a seed
is magically implanted.

08:22.102 --> 08:24.511
And nine months later...

08:24.535 --> 08:26.482
A baby is born. Here.

08:26.506 --> 08:27.984
What kind of seed?

08:28.008 --> 08:31.618
Oh, that's not important.

08:31.642 --> 08:33.520
I don't believe you.

08:33.544 --> 08:38.124
Parker, I'm your mother.
Mothers don't lie to their sons.

08:39.720 --> 08:41.698
Now go wash your hands

08:41.722 --> 08:44.222
or Santa's not gonna bring you
anything for Christmas.

08:49.529 --> 08:51.978
I just saw Edie drive off.
How long is she gonna be gone?

08:52.002 --> 08:54.140
I don't know.
She just went to show a house.

08:54.164 --> 08:55.782
Move.

08:55.806 --> 08:58.514
What's the problem?

08:58.538 --> 09:01.117
You mauled me
in Edie's bed last night.

09:01.141 --> 09:03.219
I think that deserves
a conversation.

09:03.243 --> 09:06.560
Well, what's there to talk
about? I'm just a fool in love.

09:06.584 --> 09:09.596
Oh, no! You don't mean that.

09:09.620 --> 09:12.929
Yes, I do. Look, I realize
my timing's a little off.

09:12.953 --> 09:14.300
A little?

09:14.324 --> 09:17.538
Ugh... the helium hasn't even
gone out of the balloons

09:17.562 --> 09:18.965
from your engagement party.

09:18.989 --> 09:23.610
Okay... When are you
gonna tell Edie? Tell her what?

09:23.634 --> 09:25.081
That the wedding's off. Is it?

09:25.105 --> 09:27.574
Well, isn't it? It's up to you.

09:27.598 --> 09:29.545
Are... are you saying...

09:29.569 --> 09:31.678
That you're gonna
go through with this wedding...

09:31.702 --> 09:33.680
Unless I tell you not to?

09:33.704 --> 09:35.687
Just give me a commitment,
susie q.,

09:35.711 --> 09:38.655
and I'll put a bullet in
Edie. This is insane!

09:38.679 --> 09:41.327
Come on.

09:41.351 --> 09:43.730
All this can be yours again.

09:43.754 --> 09:47.163
Just say the word...
And I let go.

09:47.187 --> 09:49.966
Oh, no! No, don't you dare!

09:49.990 --> 09:52.999
You know you want me to.
Just say it, susie q.

09:53.023 --> 09:55.642
You're...

09:55.666 --> 09:56.673
Sick!

09:59.369 --> 10:02.078
Zach,
I'm going to the drugstore.

10:02.102 --> 10:04.611
I'll be back in 20 minutes.

10:04.635 --> 10:06.913
Whoa!

10:06.937 --> 10:08.707
Oh!

10:21.792 --> 10:24.701
Paul?!

10:24.725 --> 10:28.675
I was making cookies, and I
heard the most sickening thud.

10:28.699 --> 10:30.306
Are you okay?

10:30.330 --> 10:31.778
There's...

10:31.802 --> 10:34.010
Shortening on my doorstep.

10:34.034 --> 10:35.642
Shortening?

10:35.666 --> 10:38.715
That's the last thing
you'd want on your front porch.

10:38.739 --> 10:41.009
It's meant for baking.

10:56.186 --> 11:00.206
She is so adorable,
and I just love the name Lily.

11:00.230 --> 11:01.708
It was my grandmother's name.

11:01.732 --> 11:03.810
So how you holding up?
You must be exhausted.

11:03.834 --> 11:06.821
You know, I'm a little tired, but it's
not too bad. Oh, wait a couple months.

11:06.845 --> 11:09.776
She'll start
sleeping through the night.

11:09.800 --> 11:11.778
Oh, honey, please.
Do I look like a masochist?

11:11.802 --> 11:13.780
Firs thing tomorrow, I'm hiring
a nanny and a night nurse.

11:13.804 --> 11:15.651
No, we're not.

11:15.675 --> 11:18.654
My husband, the comedian.

11:18.678 --> 11:21.057
I'm serious. I don't want
some stranger raising our baby.

11:21.081 --> 11:23.059
Well, you guys are busy.
We should go.

11:23.083 --> 11:24.861
Mm-hmm.

11:24.885 --> 11:27.433
No, it's okay.
I'll win this battle later.

11:27.457 --> 11:30.236
We are not gonna be
some yuppie couple

11:30.260 --> 11:33.700
pawning off our kid on other
people. End of discussion.

11:33.724 --> 11:35.011
Yeah, you should go.

11:35.035 --> 11:36.703
Yeah. Okay, bye.

11:36.727 --> 11:37.727
Good luck.

11:41.701 --> 11:45.151
Put down the burrito.

11:45.175 --> 11:48.154
What is all this crap
about me not getting help?

11:48.178 --> 11:51.157
Look, a brand-new baby
needs to bond with its mother.

11:51.181 --> 11:53.920
The church knows it, science
knows it, nature knows it.

11:53.944 --> 11:56.798
We have the money. What is wrong
with getting a little help?

11:56.822 --> 11:58.795
Then I'll be able
to relax once in a while,

11:58.819 --> 12:00.326
and I'll be able
tobea better mother.

12:00.350 --> 12:02.328
You wanna be a better mother?

12:02.352 --> 12:04.370
Do what mymamádid...
Make sacrifices.

12:04.394 --> 12:06.738
Mymamáworked her fingers
to the bone for me.

12:06.762 --> 12:09.257
And that's what put her
in an early grave!

12:11.261 --> 12:14.431
Well, that
and the hit-and-run thing.

12:22.342 --> 12:25.226
Look, I don't know why
you want to be emancipated,

12:25.250 --> 12:27.994
and I don't know what you've
been doing to drive him crazy.

12:28.018 --> 12:30.256
Bottom line... it's over.

12:30.280 --> 12:34.180
It's now time for you two
to kiss and make up.

12:35.786 --> 12:39.035
And just how
are we supposed to do that?

12:39.059 --> 12:41.107
Here's a thought...

12:41.131 --> 12:43.469
Just look each other
in the eye and say,

12:43.493 --> 12:45.003
"I forgive you."

12:47.767 --> 12:50.276
That'syour solution?

12:50.300 --> 12:51.778
It's actually
a technique invented

12:51.802 --> 12:53.749
by this Dutch therapist.

12:53.773 --> 12:55.251
I saw him on TV.

12:55.275 --> 12:57.523
He says,
if you verbalize forgiveness,

12:57.547 --> 13:01.387
the brain can trick the heart
into letting go of resentment.

13:01.411 --> 13:02.889
It really works.

13:02.913 --> 13:04.900
I did it with our cleaning lady.

13:04.924 --> 13:09.395
Um, I'm sorry, dad, but I think
my relationship with Andrew

13:09.419 --> 13:11.838
is just a bit more complicated
than...

13:11.862 --> 13:14.140
Would it kill you
to at least try?

13:14.164 --> 13:16.873
I'll do it... For you, grandpa.

13:16.897 --> 13:19.827
That's my boy. Bree?

13:22.402 --> 13:24.150
Fine!

13:24.174 --> 13:27.884
Yes, um...
So, um, who goes first?

13:27.908 --> 13:30.878
Either or. Doesn't matter.

13:32.512 --> 13:36.092
Mom, I forgive you.

13:36.116 --> 13:39.086
Andrew, I forgive you.

13:40.450 --> 13:42.899
That wasn't so hard, was it?

13:42.923 --> 13:46.107
Now don't expect
to feel differently right away.

13:46.131 --> 13:49.976
It takes a while. It took me
a week to forgive Esperanza.

13:50.000 --> 13:53.910
But now she's like family
again. Family who stole from us.

13:53.934 --> 13:56.321
So let's get back
to the way we were,

13:56.345 --> 14:00.917
and forget all this nonsense
about emancipation.

14:00.941 --> 14:01.941
Um...

14:04.244 --> 14:08.224
Well, grandpa, I'm... I'm still
gonna need my trust fund.

14:08.248 --> 14:10.326
You see,
I-I can't live in a place

14:10.350 --> 14:12.350
where I... I don't feel safe.

14:13.924 --> 14:15.537
What are you talking about?

14:15.561 --> 14:18.385
Well, could you live
with a woman who hits you?

14:20.390 --> 14:23.609
Bree! I slapped him once,
and he deserved it.

14:23.633 --> 14:26.017
Well, I just asked her
to stop drinking.

14:26.041 --> 14:27.073
You were drinking?

14:27.097 --> 14:30.076
She's in a.A.
Her sponsor has long hair.

14:30.100 --> 14:31.978
Andrew,
I find your concern ironic,

14:32.002 --> 14:33.980
given how tanked you were
when you ran over

14:34.004 --> 14:36.391
our neighbor's mother
with your car.

14:36.415 --> 14:39.555
Is she okay? She's dead!

14:39.579 --> 14:41.027
Well...

14:41.051 --> 14:43.990
Mom watched as her boyfriend
committed suicide.

14:44.014 --> 14:46.401
Andhe was the same guy
who killed dad!

14:46.425 --> 14:50.466
Andrew falsely accused me
of molestation...

14:50.490 --> 14:53.090
In a mall!

14:55.495 --> 14:58.074
You know,
the technique works best

14:58.098 --> 15:00.168
if you don't talk right away.

15:03.403 --> 15:06.560
Okay, let's go. I don't wanna
be late for the movie.

15:06.584 --> 15:09.376
Oh, those are pretty.
Who sent those?

15:11.011 --> 15:11.988
What?

15:12.012 --> 15:14.490
"Say the word and I'm yours.
Love, Karl."

15:14.514 --> 15:16.427
Mom, I knew this would happen

15:16.451 --> 15:18.224
when you started
hanging around together,

15:18.248 --> 15:20.226
all of your old feelings
resurfacing.

15:20.250 --> 15:21.928
No, hisfeelings.

15:21.952 --> 15:24.070
He'sthe one
with the feelings, not me.

15:24.094 --> 15:25.431
Uh-huh.

15:25.455 --> 15:28.104
Okay, don't "uh-huh" me. You're
not old enough to do that.

15:28.128 --> 15:30.106
Oh, no?
Well, how do you like this...

15:30.130 --> 15:33.379
I'm not gonna go to the movies with
you. You're gonna make me go by myself?

15:33.403 --> 15:35.386
Well, you could always
ask dad to go.

15:35.410 --> 15:37.383
In fact,
if you love him so much,

15:37.407 --> 15:39.085
why don't you marry him?

15:39.109 --> 15:41.117
Oh, wait, you already did.
Twice.

15:59.129 --> 16:02.059
Hey, Carol,
come on. Sit with us.

16:08.999 --> 16:10.476
Oh, you know what?

16:10.500 --> 16:12.979
I think we're gonna need
some napkins with this.

16:13.003 --> 16:15.221
Oh, okay, I'll go back. Thanks.

16:15.245 --> 16:17.683
My ex-boyfriend's here.
If he sees me alone, I'll die.

16:17.707 --> 16:19.685
I'm begging you, please,
act like you know me.

16:19.709 --> 16:22.188
Susan? Hey!

16:22.212 --> 16:24.660
Mike, hi!
What a surprise.

16:24.684 --> 16:28.964
How are ya? Good.

16:28.988 --> 16:31.567
Oh! God, I... I'm being so rude.

16:31.591 --> 16:35.201
Um, Mike,
I-I want you to meet...

16:35.225 --> 16:37.473
Orson hodge.

16:37.497 --> 16:40.376
Nice to meet you, Mike.

16:40.400 --> 16:42.078
Wow, I can't believe

16:42.102 --> 16:44.372
I'm finally seeing
the man himself in the flesh.

16:46.376 --> 16:49.655
So... how'd you two meet?

16:49.679 --> 16:52.418
Oh, god, I've been
her dentist for years.

16:53.613 --> 16:55.596
But last week,
I was looking in her mouth

16:55.620 --> 16:57.593
and decided
to stick my tongue in it.

17:01.591 --> 17:03.751
I'll see ya, Susan.

17:07.597 --> 17:09.575
